}}The Fijiyama plugin is a registration and alignment tool for multimodal / multi-time series of 3d images (IRM / RX / Photo / Microscopy). This tool align and combine series of 3d images. Transforms can be estimated using two algorithms : an "iconic" one, based on SimpleItk library (www.itk.org) and a "iconic and geometric" one, Block-matching, well-suited for the complex task of multi-modal registration.

==Installation of the plugin==
To install the plugin, you can use the update site to simply add it to your current Fiji distribution

==Plugin features==

* Two images registration (training / settings mode)

* N-times / M-modalities 3d series registration (main feature)

* Composition of successives Itk transforms

* Transformation of a 3d image (or a 4d / 5d hyperimage) with an Itk transform

