===Prepare your data===
To begin with the training mode (or simply register two images), you can use the provided example dataset : blabla. To begin with your data, collect two images of the same object, seen with different imaging tools, or at different observation times. Set these two images in an identified and specific location of your computer. Prepare also an empty directory, that will be used to store your work : the step you did, intermediate results, and final results. This way, it will be easy to save the current registration experiment, leave the plugin, and restore the experiment state later.

===Two image registration===
Start the plugin using the blabla button, and check "Two images registration". Follow the instructions to define input data and output directory. Once the registration manager is started, try the buttons, and read the "tooltip" appearing, until you feel comfortable to begin. 

The main elements of the registration manager are :
* Black log window : this log window guides you, telling what has been done, and what can be done right now

* Settings menus and buttons : useful to set the parameters of the future action to run

* Action buttons : Run, undo, abort drive the lifecycle of the action you selected using the settings menus

* Actions list : this list stores the past (or future) actions on the registration pathway


